Assume there is a path in \(\hat{G}\) between \((f(W),g(W))\) and \((f(W^{\prime}),g(W^{\prime}))\) of length at most \(\ell^{\prime}\). We construct a reconfiguration path \((W_{0},\dots,W_{\ell^{\prime}})\) such that \(W_{0}=W\), \(W_{\ell^{\prime}}=W^{\prime}\) and for every \(j\in\{0,\dots,\ell^{\prime}\},t\in\mathcal{T}\), it holds that \(f(W_{j})[t]=|(\mathsf{C}_{t}\cap W_{j})\setminus W^{\prime}|\) and \(g(W_{j})[t]=|(\mathsf{C}_{t}\cap W_{j})\cap W^{\prime}|\).

